 violence in the elderly and in those dependent on nursing care.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aAlter. 4aDemenz. 4aGewalt. 4aHausarzt. 4aMenschenrecht. 4aPflegebedürftigkeit. 4aPrävention. 4aRechtsmedizin. 7aMEDICAL / Geriatrics.2bisacsh  aViolence.  acare dependency.  adementia.  aforensic medicine.  ahuman rights.  aold age.  aprevention.  aprimary care doctor.1 aAbraham, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüscher, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEggert, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartwig, Sven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuhlmey, Adelheid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuhlmey, Adelheid, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMahler, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeise, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinwand, Dominique Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwedler, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuhr, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuhr, Ralf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSulmann, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeubner, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVorderwülbecke, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZank, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZenz